      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The Inland Empire Railway Co.\nhas let contract for grading por-\nton of its line into Moscow, Idaho,\nto Harry Woods. The distance COW\ncred by the contract is about a mile\nand three quarters and includes the\ndepot grounds in Moscow. 1t is re-\nported that all grading contracts\nthat have been awarded by the cleo\ntrio line people on the line from\nPalouse to Moscow provide that\nthey must be finished on or before\nJune 1. This indicates that the\nintention of the company is to\nhave their trains into Moscow by\nJuly |.\n\n\nThe track is now laid from Pa\nlouise to Garfield and the crew is\nworking through the latter place.\nElectric trains are expected to be\nrunning into Garfield by April 1."
    }
  ]
